#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:4
msgid "Storage Patterns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:10
msgid ""
"This is example code for learning purposes. Do not use in production without "
"thorough review and testing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:12
msgid ""
"Let's start with a minimal contract that demonstrates state storage. This "
"contract stores a single integer that can be set by anyone."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:16
msgid "Simple Storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:18
msgid ""
"#pragma version >0.3.10\n"
"\n"
"storedData: public(int128)\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(_x: int128):\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def set(_x: int128):\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:22
msgid "This example shows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:24
msgid "A public state variable ``storedData`` with an auto-generated getter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:25
msgid "A constructor (``__init__``) that sets the initial value"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:26
msgid "An external function ``set()`` that modifies state"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:28
msgid ""
"The ``public`` modifier on ``storedData`` automatically creates a getter "
"function, so external contracts can read the value by calling ``contract."
"storedData()``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:36
msgid "Advanced Storage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:38
msgid ""
"Building on the simple storage example, this contract adds input validation, "
"events, and a reset function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:41
msgid ""
"#pragma version >0.3.10\n"
"\n"
"event DataChange:\n"
"    setter: indexed(address)\n"
"    value: int128\n"
"\n"
"storedData: public(int128)\n"
"\n"
"@deploy\n"
"def __init__(_x: int128):\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def set(_x: int128):\n"
"  assert _x >= 0, \"No negative values\"\n"
"  assert self.storedData < 100, \"Storage is locked when 100 or more is "
"stored\"\n"
"  self.storedData = _x\n"
"  log DataChange(setter=msg.sender, value=_x)\n"
"\n"
"@external\n"
"def reset():\n"
"  self.storedData = 0\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:45
msgid "New concepts introduced:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:47
msgid ""
"**Events**: The ``DataChange`` event logs who changed the value and what "
"they changed it to. The ``indexed`` keyword allows filtering by the setter's "
"address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:48
msgid ""
"**Assertions with messages**: ``assert _x >= 0, \"No negative values\"`` "
"reverts with a readable error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vyper-by-example/storage.rst:49
msgid ""
"**Business logic guards**: The contract locks when the stored value reaches "
"100."
msgstr ""

